1109127887876222979.text: Little Susie Server smiled. The lemmings would go out and buy their boxes. They would think they invested in a chonker. They would never know otherwise. #HappyFriday!

1109127682644684800.text: Well, if the hpc monster is 1 exaflop and the box is 2 petaflops (each at a cost of 400k) you would need 500 of them at a cost of 200 million to be on par. And they would be separate clusters, totally different beasties from the connected brain of the exascale computer.

1109127424325890048.text: But little Susie Server, she was not convinced by the prowess, and good thing that she brought her power of free thinking with her that day. How many of these boxes would it take to match or supersede the exascale computer?
